This paper deals with fairness in decision making by AI systems, which is a common topic in the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The proposed algorithm also uses contextual information about the users and the task, which is a key aspect of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses empirical results from an online user study, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Additionally, the paper deals with allocation decisions, which could fall under the category of control theory (cs.CY) or social and information networks (cs.SI).
